# closed_loop_glitch.m8script — Task 7 Phase 1: build a glitchy patch
# Load TEST-FILE, crank instrument 02's (MAC, MacroSynth) AMP to max, save,
# render.
#
# Fixed 2026-07-18 (M8_APP_AUTOMATION_SPEC.md Tier 4 notes). This script
# previously (a) never dismissed TEST-FILE's missing-samples overlay, whose
# dismiss handler swallows the very next keydown -- throwing off all 3
# `key SHIFT+RIGHT` presses by one and landing on PHRASE 20, not the
# Instrument screen; (b) used `key X; hold UP 255; key X`, which does not
# edit Instrument-screen fields at all -- editHeld is only true between X's
# own down/up events, and that sequence spans multiple frames, so it's
# already false by the time UP fires; and (c) its own navigation comment
# ("Down to NAME, Down to TRANSP, Right to AMP") was wrong for the intended
# target and, combined with (a), landed on an unrelated field of instrument
# 01 (a WavSynth, "WAV") -- itself mishandled by InstrumentScreen.cpp, which
# only branches on isMac and always displays/reads inst.sampler.* regardless
# of the instrument's real type, so edits to a Wav/Hyper/FM instrument's
# shared fields are invisible on screen even though EngineStateUpdater
# correctly writes them (confirmed by instrumentation: type=4/WAVSYNTH,
# isWav=1, wav.amp went 0->1 while the displayed sampler.amp stayed 0).
# All three confirmed by reproduction with intermediate dump_screen/
# dump_json calls.
#
# The original "crank AMP -> glitch" narrative also turned out to be
# misleading even once mechanically correct: TEST-FILE.m8s fails
# m8_analyze's crest/DC checks *unedited* (confirmed directly: crest 3.61 dB,
# DC-worst 0.063, both well past the hard-fail thresholds) -- a known,
# documented gap (status.md Known Issues): instrument 02 ("MAC", MacroSynth)
# has no volume envelope in the file and drones continuously for the whole
# render. Instrument 00's AMP (what the old script's comment described) was
# never the cause. This script now targets instrument 02 directly (song
# track column 1, confirmed via the render event CSV: track=1 plays
# instrument=2) and cranks *its* AMP from a confirmed 0x00 baseline to 0xFF,
# which genuinely amplifies the existing drone rather than merely riding on
# TEST-FILE's pre-existing failure coincidentally.

load third_party/m8-files-cxx/examples/songs/TEST-FILE.m8s
wait 5

# Dismiss the missing-samples overlay (its first-keydown-after-load is
# otherwise swallowed by main.cpp's overlay-dismiss handler).
key DOWN
wait 1

# Move to song track column 1 (0-indexed), then drill down to its
# instrument (02, MAC/MacroSynth).
key RIGHT
key SHIFT+RIGHT
key SHIFT+RIGHT
key SHIFT+RIGHT
wait 2
assert_screen contains "INST. 02"
assert_field TYPE MACROSYN

# Navigate to AMP: TYPE->NAME->TRANSP->SHAPE (3 downs), then SHAPE->AMP
# (1 right) -- see GetMacrosynNavMap in InstrumentMacrosynLayout.h.
key DOWN
key DOWN
key DOWN
key RIGHT
wait 1
assert_field AMP 00

# Max out AMP (compound key+direction: X-down, UP-down, UP-up, X-up all in
# one frame, so editHeld is still true when UP fires -- see
# synth_macrosynth.m8script for the same idiom)
repeat 255 {
    key X+UP
}
wait 2
assert_field AMP FF

# Save and render
save artifacts/glitch.m8s
render 2 glitch.wav
